Since you are coming from an "APK" mindset, keep in mind:

No Multi-tasking: By default, when your app runs, the Wii U OS is "suspended." You have full control of the hardware, but you have to handle everything (input, sound, graphics) yourself.

The Gamepad: It’s a second screen! It has its own resolution (854×480) and touch input. It’s one of the coolest parts to program for.

